<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="274" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1050,1329]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1087,1113]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Remarks.</emphasis>
First records from 
<collectingCountry box="[537,637,1087,1113]" name="Hungary" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Hungary</collectingCountry>
. This species is known from many countries of the Palaearctic region; among them 
<collectingCountry box="[302,400,1123,1149]" name="Hungary" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Hungary</collectingCountry>
is also listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yu, D. S. &amp; van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K." box="[597,783,1123,1149]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274" refId="ref7112" refString="Yu, D. S., van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K. (2016) Taxapad 2016, Ichneumonoidea 2015. Nepean, Ontario. Database on flash-drive. Available from: http: // www. taxapad. com" type="url" year="2016">
Yu 
<emphasis box="[638,689,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, citing 
<bibRefCitation author="Strobl, G." box="[869,1024,1123,1149]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274" pagination="43 - 79" refId="ref6848" refString="Strobl, G. (1901) Hymenoptera aus Ungarn und Siebenburgen. Gesammelt von Professor Gabriel Strobl und Professor Thalhammer. Verhandlungen und Mitteilungen des Siebenburgischen Vereins fur Naturwissenschaften in Hermannstadt, 50, 43 - 79." type="journal article" year="1901">Strobl (1901)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dalla Torre, C. G." box="[1038,1251,1123,1149]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274" refId="ref5839" refString="Dalla Torre, C. G. (1902) Catalogus Hymenopterorum. Volumen III. Trigonalidae, Megalyridae, Stephanidae, Ichneumonidae, Agriotypidae, Evaniidae, Pelecinidae. Guilelmi Engelmann. G. Engelmann, Lipsiae, 1141 pp." type="book" year="1902">Dalla Torre (1902)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Zilahi-Kiss, A." pageId="6" pageNumber="274" pagination="32 - 146" refId="ref7157" refString="Zilahi-Kiss, A. (1924) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der ungarischen und siebenburgischen Ichneumoniden- (Schlupfwespen-) Fauna. Verhandlungen und Mitteilungen des Siebenburgischen Vereins fur Naturwissenschaften in Hermannstadt, 72 - 74, 32 - 146." type="journal article" year="1924">Zilahi-Kiss (1924)</bibRefCitation>
. However, the locality (Götzenberg) in 
<bibRefCitation author="Strobl, G." box="[683,835,1159,1185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274" pagination="43 - 79" refId="ref6848" refString="Strobl, G. (1901) Hymenoptera aus Ungarn und Siebenburgen. Gesammelt von Professor Gabriel Strobl und Professor Thalhammer. Verhandlungen und Mitteilungen des Siebenburgischen Vereins fur Naturwissenschaften in Hermannstadt, 50, 43 - 79." type="journal article" year="1901">Strobl (1901)</bibRefCitation>
refers to 
<collectingCountry box="[946,1031,1159,1185]" name="Austria" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Austria</collectingCountry>
, not to 
<collectingCountry box="[1120,1219,1159,1185]" name="Hungary" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Hungary</collectingCountry>
, and no Hungarian localities are mentioned in 
<bibRefCitation author="Dalla Torre, C. G." box="[463,676,1195,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274" refId="ref5839" refString="Dalla Torre, C. G. (1902) Catalogus Hymenopterorum. Volumen III. Trigonalidae, Megalyridae, Stephanidae, Ichneumonidae, Agriotypidae, Evaniidae, Pelecinidae. Guilelmi Engelmann. G. Engelmann, Lipsiae, 1141 pp." type="book" year="1902">Dalla Torre (1902)</bibRefCitation>
at all. The localities given in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zilahi-Kiss, A." box="[1023,1233,1195,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="274" pagination="32 - 146" refId="ref7157" refString="Zilahi-Kiss, A. (1924) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der ungarischen und siebenburgischen Ichneumoniden- (Schlupfwespen-) Fauna. Verhandlungen und Mitteilungen des Siebenburgischen Vereins fur Naturwissenschaften in Hermannstadt, 72 - 74, 32 - 146." type="journal article" year="1924">Zilahi-Kiss (1924)</bibRefCitation>
refer to 
<collectingCountry box="[1335,1436,1195,1221]" name="Romania" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Romania</collectingCountry>
(Enyed = Aiud, Remete = Râmeț, Oroszmező = Rus, Csicsókeresztur = Cristeștii Ciceului, Désakna = Ocna Dejului) and 
<collectingCountry box="[199,271,1267,1293]" name="Serbia" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Serbia</collectingCountry>
(Versecz = 
<collectingRegion box="[405,473,1267,1293]" country="Serbia" name="Vrsac" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Vršac</collectingRegion>
), not to 
<collectingCountry box="[565,667,1267,1293]" name="Hungary" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Hungary</collectingCountry>
; these specimens were not found in HNHM, their identifications are impossible to validate. Hence, the records given above are to be considered the first ones from 
<collectingCountry box="[1215,1315,1303,1329]" name="Hungary" pageId="6" pageNumber="274">Hungary</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
